573
00:42:19,883 --> 00:42:21,884
If you know Kate, you know Kate's heroes.

574
00:42:22,505 --> 00:42:25,286
Kate loves strength, she loves misfits,

575
00:42:25,606 --> 00:42:26,707
and she loves rebels.

576
00:42:27,227 --> 00:42:28,328
She loves them so much

577
00:42:28,428 --> 00:42:30,068
that she frequently dresses like them.

578
00:42:30,729 --> 00:42:33,790
Kate's Thor cosplay is some of the most beautiful.

579
00:42:34,210 --> 00:42:37,754
powerful costuming I've seen outside of an actual Hemsworth.

580
00:42:38,194 --> 00:42:41,057
In the 90s, when Microsoft and Ensemble Studios

581
00:42:41,117 --> 00:42:43,319
released the first Age of Empires game,

582
00:42:43,719 --> 00:42:45,040
it contained a grievous error.

583
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:48,243
For totally benign reasons, the game misrepresented

584
00:42:48,263 --> 00:42:50,686
a crucial point of cultural history,

585
00:42:50,786 --> 00:42:52,447
an error that was so egregious

586
00:42:52,527 --> 00:42:55,870
that a regional executive of ours was actually put in jail.

587
00:42:56,829 --> 00:43:01,311
We needed a hero. We needed somebody to help us fix our problem.

588
00:43:01,671 --> 00:43:05,533
We needed somebody maybe from Asgard sent to save us from ourselves.

589
00:43:05,593 --> 00:43:08,955
And that's when I got to meet my favorite geographer, Kate Edwards.

590
00:43:09,275 --> 00:43:14,898
Kate is a rare being, a leader introvert. As a kid, Kate would frequently look up

591
00:43:14,998 --> 00:43:18,760
from wandering the playground in a reverie to notice other children following her.

592
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,821
And she would demand, why? Why are you following me around?

593
00:43:22,662 --> 00:43:24,624
But to me, the answer is obvious.

594
00:43:25,024 --> 00:43:26,486
Kate is never lost.

595
00:43:26,706 --> 00:43:28,948
Born into a loving and supportive family,

596
00:43:29,329 --> 00:43:31,331
her parents established a morality

597
00:43:31,411 --> 00:43:33,253
based on doing the right thing,

598
00:43:33,473 --> 00:43:34,494
defending the little guy,

599
00:43:34,775 --> 00:43:36,416
and taking action where possible

600
00:43:36,817 --> 00:43:39,239
that forms the basis of Kate's worldview today.

601
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:41,622
At Microsoft, Kate led the entire company

602
00:43:41,762 --> 00:43:43,864
in the establishment of a set of processes

603
00:43:44,185 --> 00:43:50,334
for geopolitical reviews and standards that is the basis for our friendly global relationships

604
00:43:50,534 --> 00:43:53,198
and authentic cultural representation today.

605
00:43:53,659 --> 00:43:56,803
And yes, Kate did help us get our executive out of jail.

606
00:43:57,424 --> 00:43:58,746
As director of the IGDA,

607
00:43:59,387 --> 00:44:04,212
Kate broadened both her global worldview and also her understanding of the games industry.

608
00:44:04,572 --> 00:44:09,677
She also gained fame for her outspoken opinions on the imbalances and the injustices

609
00:44:09,897 --> 00:44:12,640
that threaten independent game developers even today.

610
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:15,923
She formed a kind of Dumbledore's army of advocates.

611
00:44:16,483 --> 00:44:19,605
focusing on topics ranging from crunch to diversity

612
00:44:19,805 --> 00:44:21,525
to safety from online hate mobs.

613
00:44:21,805 --> 00:44:23,746
Kate expanded the reach of the IGDA

614
00:44:23,806 --> 00:44:25,747
to emerging game development regions

615
00:44:25,807 --> 00:44:29,028
like Bangladesh, Tunisia, Egypt, and many others.

616
00:44:29,328 --> 00:44:32,389
And her advocacy hasn't ended in the years post-IGDA.

617
00:44:32,489 --> 00:44:36,230
Last year alone, Kate traveled to more than 25 countries,

618
00:44:36,730 --> 00:44:40,792
and she spent more than 76 hours on stage or in panels

619
00:44:40,972 --> 00:44:43,192
inspiring game developers everywhere.

620
00:44:43,392 --> 00:44:44,253
Her global focus

621
00:44:44,533 --> 00:44:48,860
is what makes her so perfect for the Executive Director of the Global Game Jam.

622
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:53,788
Although she has confided in me, she believes it's time to expand Global Game Jam's horizons.

623
00:44:54,509 --> 00:44:58,616
Somewhere in a galaxy far, far away, the Rebels need our help.

