630
00:45:24,772 --> 00:45:27,334
obviously because we're all aware of global events at the moment,

631
00:45:27,834 --> 00:45:30,116
I am glad that we can at least connect via the stream.

632
00:45:30,316 --> 00:45:33,978
As game creators and as people who live in a digital world,

633
00:45:34,018 --> 00:45:36,960
we have the ability to maintain this connection no matter what.

634
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:39,482
So we are very resilient in that way.

635
00:45:40,142 --> 00:45:47,130
And so as I'm standing here in Hoth, in actual Finnsund, Norway, where they filmed the Empire Strikes Back over 40 years ago,

636
00:45:47,150 --> 00:45:54,199
I wanted to share just a few quick thoughts to you about what this award means to me and what it means to the industry.

637
00:45:55,472 --> 00:45:59,933
You know, when we talk about being an ambassador and what that means,

638
00:46:00,593 --> 00:46:04,574
you know, it's about putting our best self forward and trying to present the

639
00:46:04,634 --> 00:46:08,455
industry in the best light and to make change happen for the better.

640
00:46:08,475 --> 00:46:11,416
And, you know, what does it really mean to make change?

641
00:46:11,556 --> 00:46:14,897
I think for a lot of us, you know, we find that challenging today

642
00:46:14,977 --> 00:46:16,917
because we don't really know where to start.

643
00:46:17,517 --> 00:46:20,618
And I think in my own experience, where it really starts is with ourselves.

644
00:46:20,758 --> 00:46:21,478
If we can.

645
00:46:21,999 --> 00:46:27,722
figure out what is stopping us from taking that step to help somebody or to take that step forward

646
00:46:27,762 --> 00:46:33,286
or to be a voice for someone who's marginalized. You know we have to find the confidence in

647
00:46:33,366 --> 00:46:38,370
ourselves to get over our imposter syndrome and get to that point where we have that confidence.

648
00:46:38,770 --> 00:46:41,592
You know whether you actually believe in that confidence or not,

649
00:46:42,032 --> 00:46:46,235
it's more about believing in the reason to have that confidence which is for other people.

650
00:46:46,935 --> 00:46:49,777
And I know in my experience, that's what's really been driving me.

651
00:46:49,817 --> 00:46:55,859
I mean, I have been driven for a long time now by this notion that evil triumphs when good people do nothing.

652
00:46:56,279 --> 00:47:01,181
And I really believe that. And so that's what has been driving my action in this industry.

653
00:47:01,542 --> 00:47:04,783
Because I want people to be better and I want the industry to be better.

654
00:47:04,803 --> 00:47:13,286
And I want us to treat each other with more respect and to treat each other with fairness and being inclusive in how we approach everything.

655
00:47:14,156 --> 00:47:17,937
You know, at one point, John F. Kennedy, the former U.S. President, said,

656
00:47:17,997 --> 00:47:24,459
if not us, then who? And if not now, then when? And really, I think that's something that all of

657
00:47:24,539 --> 00:47:29,561
us need to challenge ourselves with. When we see something that we don't like, when we see something

658
00:47:29,621 --> 00:47:34,662
that we are dissatisfied with in this industry, and it could be a huge issue that affects all of

659
00:47:34,762 --> 00:47:39,224
us, or it could be a tiny thing that affects your local community, you have to ask yourself,

660
00:47:39,884 --> 00:47:41,145
Why is it not changing?

661
00:47:41,605 --> 00:47:43,705
And then how can you be that agent of change

662
00:47:43,745 --> 00:47:44,526
to make it happen?

663
00:47:44,926 --> 00:47:46,226
And you know, in my experience,

664
00:47:46,286 --> 00:47:47,647
and I think what people have seen,

665
00:47:48,207 --> 00:47:49,448
at least in my actions,

666
00:47:50,108 --> 00:47:51,908
is that basically I made a decision

667
00:47:51,968 --> 00:47:53,989
that I'm gonna be the one to step forward

668
00:47:54,029 --> 00:47:55,570
and actually try and make change happen.

669
00:47:56,030 --> 00:47:57,710
It's not because I'm better than anybody.

670
00:47:57,791 --> 00:48:00,111
It's not because I have more experience than anybody.

671
00:48:00,491 --> 00:48:02,252
It's just, it's a simple act of will.

