00:59:35,103 --> 00:59:38,666
The first time Roberta Williams played Colossal Cave Adventure, she was transfixed.

842
00:59:39,427 --> 00:59:41,989
It was a computer game unlike anything she'd ever played before.

843
00:59:42,249 --> 00:59:44,111
Literary, narrative, fantastical.

844
00:59:44,949 --> 00:59:48,131
She burned through that game, then others, and when she ran out of games altogether,

845
00:59:48,171 --> 00:59:49,572
she took matters into her own hands.

846
00:59:50,053 --> 00:59:52,234
She sat down at her kitchen table and designed her own.

847
00:59:52,795 --> 00:59:56,137
It was 1979, and Roberta Williams was 26 years old.

848
00:59:57,198 --> 01:00:00,360
From that initial moment, a truly unconventional legacy would rise.

849
01:00:01,060 --> 01:00:06,084
Born Roberta Lynn Hauer in 1953, the woman who would one day become the queen of adventure

850
01:00:06,104 --> 01:00:08,966
games grew up quietly in the suburbs of northern Los Angeles.

851
01:00:09,817 --> 01:00:11,477
That first game became Mystery House.

852
01:00:11,977 --> 01:00:15,498
Her husband, Ken Williams, programmed the game, but she designed it and drew its images,

853
01:00:15,979 --> 01:00:20,340
making Mystery House not just the first adventure game with graphics, but one of the earliest

854
01:00:20,400 --> 01:00:23,181
examples of a separation between programmer and designer.

855
01:00:24,001 --> 01:00:28,042
In a moment when most people didn't know what personal computers were good for, Roberta

856
01:00:28,082 --> 01:00:31,804
and Ken Williams would strike out on their own adventure to press the limits of computing

857
01:00:31,844 --> 01:00:32,904
in the name of entertainment.

858
01:00:33,724 --> 01:00:37,766
Together, they founded Sierra Online, a company that needs no introduction in the annals of

859
01:00:37,806 --> 01:00:38,606
video game history.

860
01:00:39,449 --> 01:00:43,331
For much of the 1980s and 90s, Sierra was the largest publisher of home entertainment

861
01:00:43,351 --> 01:00:47,873
software in the world, and flagship among its titles was Roberta's King's Quest series,

862
01:00:48,353 --> 01:00:52,655
a bright and lively collection of eight games spanning nearly 20 years of production and

863
01:00:52,735 --> 01:00:53,916
millions of copies sold.

864
01:00:54,516 --> 01:00:59,198
Best remembered today for their surreal mashup of folklore and fable, mythology and legend.

865
01:01:00,133 --> 01:01:04,594
Only in King's Quest could Medusa share a landscape with evil wizards or Pegasus fly

866
01:01:04,654 --> 01:01:05,715
over Dracula's castle.

867
01:01:06,515 --> 01:01:09,155
Overriding each of these worlds, however, was a basic narrative.

868
01:01:09,695 --> 01:01:13,076
Find your destiny, find your family, and protect them at all costs.

869
01:01:13,916 --> 01:01:18,177
Counterposed to King's Quest are Roberta's domestic horrors, Mystery House, The Colonel's

870
01:01:18,217 --> 01:01:23,318
Bequest, and Phantasmagoria, in which families are trying to kill you and homes are places

871
01:01:23,358 --> 01:01:23,918
where you die.

872
01:01:24,579 --> 01:01:29,060
Roberta Williams' oeuvre expresses a narrative expansiveness few other designers have ever

873
01:01:29,140 --> 01:01:29,480
endeavored.

874
01:01:30,668 --> 01:01:34,571
So it's 2020, and we're here to acknowledge what Roberta Williams never doubted, that

875
01:01:34,651 --> 01:01:35,652
she was a pioneer.

876
01:01:36,452 --> 01:01:40,976
In the years since she left the game industry in 1988, she has been reluctant to embrace

877
01:01:41,036 --> 01:01:41,897
industry recognition.

878
01:01:42,737 --> 01:01:46,658
But perhaps it's we who need to give her this reward more than she needs to receive it.

879
01:01:47,178 --> 01:01:51,800
